Label: craniofacial/craniocervical phenotype
Definition: An abnormal phenotype involving the craniofacial and craniocervical regions, encompassing abnormalities in the head, face, and neck junction.

Label: embryonic development/birth phenotype
Definition: A phenotype involving the development of the embryo or fetus and conditions present at birth.

Label: mortality/aging phenotype
Definition: A mortality/aging phenotype refers to the observable characteristics and traits associated with both the processes of aging and the factors influencing mortality (death) in an organism.
